definition.value: Feingold syndrome type 1 (FS1) is a rare inherited malformation syndrome characterized by microcephaly, short stature and numerous digital anomalies.

Feingold syndrome type 2 (FS2) is a rare inherited malformation syndrome characterized by skeletal abnormalities and mild intellectual disabilities similar to those seen in Feingold syndrome type 1 (FS1; see this term) but that lacks the manifestations of gastrointestinal atresia and short palpebral fissures.

Holt-Oram syndrome (HOS) is the most common form of heart-hand syndrome (see this term) and is characterized by skeletal abnormalities of the upper limbs and mild-to-severe congenital cardiac defects.
